name: Public Health Statistics- Chlamydia cases among females aged 15-44 in Chicago, by year, 2000-2014.
description: The annual number of newly reported, laboratory-confirmed cases of chlamydia (Chlamydia trachomatis) among females aged 15-44 years and annual chlamydia incidence rate (cases per 100,000 females aged 15-44 years) with corresponding 95% confidence intervals by Chicago community area, for years 2000 – 2014.  See the full description by clicking on the maroon "About" button on the right-hand side of the screen, and click on the PDF under "Attachments".
